question
Write a function countInfinity that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the number of non-finite elements in the array.
Examples:
the countInfinity ([Infinity, 1/0, -10/0, 12]) function should return 3, since this array contains three non-finite elements: 
these are Infinity, 1/0, -10/0

solution:

function countInfinity(arr){
  let sum = 0;
    if(Number.isFinite === true) return 0;
      for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
      if(Number.isFinite (arr[i]) !== true)
  sum++;
  }
return sum;
}
